sentences: Peter Frödin (born 7 January 1964) is a Danish actor, comedian and singer.
His career began in 1984 on Merkurteatret as an actor.
Peter collaborated on Bent Fabricius-Bjerre's album Jukebox in 2004.
Frödin is openly gay، he has been in a relationship with Jon Jørgensen since 1996, they entered into a registered partnership in 2007 [1]

Peter Frödin sang a song together with Jimmy Jørgensen that was called Vent på mig and was the most played song in the radio in the period from 1995-2010.
Together with Hella Joof, he hosted a show called Bullerfnis (1990-1992).

Later he played with Paprika Steen, Hella Joof and Martin Brygmann on Cafe Teatret, which led to many years of cooperation in the comedy-groups Lex & Klatten (Saturday night satire show), and Det brune punktum.
He has had a lot of parts in Danish movies like Hannibal & Jerry, Motello, Mirakel, Grev Axel, Jul I Valhal and En kort en lang.
Peter has worked with Søren Østergaard and they've made a circus called Zirkus Nemo which is a 'comedy-circus' that tours Denmark in the summer months.
